Making w and x volatile does not remove any of the four outcomes.
The reason is that the volatile guarantees only give a happens‑before edge for reads and writes of the same variable.
In this test each thread writes one variable and reads the other variable, so no volatile‑induced happens‑before edge is created between the two threads. Consequently the program can still exhibit all four combinations, just as with plain fields.

Code snippets
Both snippets repeat the experiment until every possible output has been seen at least once.
When the set of observed results reaches size 4 the loop stops – this is guaranteed to terminate because each iteration has a non‑zero probability of producing each of the four outcomes.

